{"tid":1034694,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"義肢整到《銃夢：戰鬥天使》個女主角咁","createTime":"2019-02-24T06:18:13.000Z","updateTime":"2019-02-24T09:00:14.000Z","uid":130105,"like":3,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":12,"replies":[{"pid":"8fa5bbdf3eda67a989e3f631bc103f2d3d7883d5","tid":1034694,"uid":130105,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-02-24T06:18:13.000Z","msg":"其實幾 low tech ，香港整到啫<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/brain.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/brain.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/brain.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n===============<br />\n&bull;Aged just 15-months, little Tilly Lockey was diagnosed with meningitis which destroyed both her arms <br />\n&bull;The now 13-year-old is one of a growing group to sport HeroArms &ndash; technically advanced prosthetic <br />\n&bull;Her prosthetic have hands and wrists that move and grip like the real thing - and cost just &pound;5,000 each<br />\n&bull;Tilly could be described as the real-life Alita, the protagonist in James Cameron's new Hollywood blockbuster <br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/17/10186806-0-image-a-10_1550944698131.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F17%2F10186806-0-image-a-10_1550944698131.jpg&h=bd88ad8f&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n The latest film from the director of Titanic and Avatar was bound to attract attention, with singer Dua Lipa joining A-list actors Jennifer Connelly and Christoph Waltz on the red carpet. But all eyes were on a less familiar figure: 13-year-old Tilly Lockey<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/18/10187122-0-While_most_youngsters_her_age_might_be_overcome_by_shyness_when_-m-69_1550945890215.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F18%2F10187122-0-While_most_youngsters_her_age_might_be_overcome_by_shyness_when_-m-69_1550945890215.jpg&h=6cd52aca&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n While most youngsters her age might be overcome by shyness when faced with a wall of photographers, the teenager beamed with confidence as she posed for them. And there was something else that set her apart from the stars alongside her<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/18/10187012-0-For_Tilly_is_in_many_ways_the_real_life_Alita_a_bionic_young_wom-m-67_1550945873241.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F18%2F10187012-0-For_Tilly_is_in_many_ways_the_real_life_Alita_a_bionic_young_wom-m-67_1550945873241.jpg&h=d52e6414&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/17/10186510-0-image-a-2_1550944112558.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F17%2F10186510-0-image-a-2_1550944112558.jpg&h=8194da98&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n The schoolgirl, who lost her hands and forearms to meningitis as a baby, is one of a small but growing group to sport HeroArms &ndash; technically advanced prosthetics with hands and wrists that move and grip like the real thing <br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/17/10186492-0-image-m-7_1550944168645.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F17%2F10186492-0-image-m-7_1550944168645.jpg&h=965953df&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/17/10186494-0-image-m-9_1550944177668.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F17%2F10186494-0-image-m-9_1550944177668.jpg&h=3b484c15&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/18/10186854-0-image-a-29_1550944864985.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F18%2F10186854-0-image-a-29_1550944864985.jpg&h=4723ce0b&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Tilly was just 15 months old when mum Sarah, 39, a charity worker, heard her whimpering in her sleep. &lsquo;I thought she was teething so I gave her some Calpol,&rsquo; Sarah says. &lsquo;But the next morning she was pale and lethargic so I got an emergency appointment at the GP&rsquo;<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/18/10186850-0-image-m-25_1550944831152.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F18%2F10186850-0-image-m-25_1550944831152.jpg&h=fc44840d&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/18/10186852-0-image-m-27_1550944854342.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F18%2F10186852-0-image-m-27_1550944854342.jpg&h=1bbda980&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/18/10186882-0-image-m-41_1550944971485.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F18%2F10186882-0-image-m-41_1550944971485.jpg&h=17d1b67a&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n As Tilly grew, Sarah (far right) and Adam, also 39, tried to get Tilly to wear various prosthetics. &lsquo;The first one was a hard lump of plastic hanging off her arm that needed a type of harness round the shoulder to keep it in place,&rsquo; Sarah says. &lsquo;At three, she got her first electric hands, which moved the fingers by picking up signals from nerves in the skin. But these only allowed Tilly to move her fingers one at a time"},{"pid":"5c94cabf73175255159ed63e1ce7b191f51c6314","tid":1034694,"uid":130105,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-02-24T06:18:31.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/24/01/10186866-6737707-image-a-10_1550973271253.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F24%2F01%2F10186866-6737707-image-a-10_1550973271253.jpg&h=eaba8a90&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/18/10186864-0-image-a-38_1550944941856.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F18%2F10186864-0-image-a-38_1550944941856.jpg&h=7f605b33&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/18/10186906-0-image-m-48_1550945247186.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F18%2F10186906-0-image-m-48_1550945247186.jpg&h=4c3b8be8&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Remarkably, Tilly&rsquo;s new arms came as a gift &ndash; after Cameron&rsquo;s company approached Open Bionics, the Bristol-based firm who make them. The movie makers offered to pay for a new pair of hands for an amputee that look just like the ones Alita has<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/18/10186908-0-image-m-50_1550945262854.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F18%2F10186908-0-image-m-50_1550945262854.jpg&h=ba8a6577&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Remarkably, Tilly&rsquo;s new arms came as a gift &ndash; after Cameron&rsquo;s company approached Open Bionics, the Bristol-based firm who make them. The movie makers offered to pay for a new pair of hands for an amputee that look just like the ones Alita has<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/24/01/10186914-6737707-Tilly_is_delighted_with_her_new_found_skills_I_could_do_a_lot_be-a-9_1550973271251.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F24%2F01%2F10186914-6737707-Tilly_is_delighted_with_her_new_found_skills_I_could_do_a_lot_be-a-9_1550973271251.jpg&h=f46f0b3b&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Tilly is delighted with her new-found skills. &lsquo;I could do a lot before without hands, but it&rsquo;s fun trying out things with the HeroArm,&rsquo; she says. &lsquo;I can grip a toothbrush, use a knife and fork, brush my hair and play video games without having to tape the controller to my hand like I used to. At school, everyone wants to shake me by the hand&rsquo;<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/18/10186900-0-image-a-43_1550945226848.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F18%2F10186900-0-image-a-43_1550945226848.jpg&h=f679135b&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Using a 3D-scanner and pictures taken on an iPhone, the company can create a personalised arm within a couple of days. Early models included the &lsquo;Iron Man&rsquo; hand, a Disney &lsquo;Frozen&rsquo; hand and a Star Wars light sabre version that lit up when you moved it<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/23/18/10187440-6737707-image-a-86_1550946881449.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F23%2F18%2F10187440-6737707-image-a-86_1550946881449.jpg&h=7e10e5cb&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n As Tilly grew, Sarah and Adam, also 39, tried to get Tilly to wear various prosthetics. &lsquo;The first one was a hard lump of plastic hanging off her arm that needed a type of harness round the shoulder to keep it in place,&rsquo; Sarah says<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2019/02/24/01/10187438-6737707-Tilly_is_delighted_with_her_new_found_skills_I_could_do_a_lot_be-a-11_1550973271257.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2019%2F02%2F24%2F01%2F10187438-6737707-Tilly_is_delighted_with_her_new_found_skills_I_could_do_a_lot_be-a-11_1550973271257.jpg&h=726e072d&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Tilly is delighted with her new-found skills. &lsquo;I could do a lot before without hands, but it&rsquo;s fun trying out things with the HeroArm,&rsquo; she says. &lsquo;I can grip a toothbrush, use a knife and fork, brush my hair and play video games without having to tape the controller to my hand like I used to. At school, everyone wants to shake me by the hand&rsquo;<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://videos.dailymail.co.uk/video/mol/2019/02/12/3047277526491050009/1024x576_MP4_3047277526491050009.mp4\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fvideos.dailymail.co.uk%2Fvideo%2Fmol%2F2019%2F02%2F12%2F3047277526491050009%2F1024x576_MP4_3047277526491050009.mp4&d=5l33Zop1uuimQiJtW1o9xQ1nSF4GOVyTVdrqrZ1TEh8%3D&h=954915c2\" target=\"_blank\">https://videos.dailymail.co.uk/video/mol/2019/02/12/3047277526491050009/1024x576_MP4_3047277526491050009.mp4</a><br />\n Teenage girl uses bionic hands to deftly apply her makeup<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://videos.dailymail.co.uk/video/mol/2017/06/15/227149202021371754/1024x576_MP4_227149202021371754.mp4\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fvideos.dailymail.co.uk%2Fvideo%2Fmol%2F2017%2F06%2F15%2F227149202021371754%2F1024x576_MP4_227149202021371754.mp4&d=5l33Zop1uuimQiJtW1o9xQ1nSF4GOVyTVdrqrZ1TEh8%3D&h=1aae79c1\" target=\"_blank\">https://videos.dailymail.co.uk/video/mol/2017/06/15/227149202021371754/1024x576_MP4_227149202021371754.mp4</a><br />\n 11 Year old Tilly is helping to pioneer bionic limb advancements<br />\n<br />\nsource:<a href=\"https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-6737707/Bionic-girl-Tilly-Lockey.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailymail.co.uk%2Fnews%2Farticle-6737707%2FBionic-girl-Tilly-Lockey.html&d=5l33Zop1uuimQiJtW1o9xQ1nSF4GOVyTVdrqrZ1TEh8%3D&h=ee1f3c0f\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-6737707/Bionic-girl-Tilly-Lockey.html</a>"},{"pid":"fce22da61ba3bc28de4fddeccb67f3d873554437","tid":1034694,"uid":93986,"like":19,"dislike":0,"score":19,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-02-24T06:20:30.000Z","msg":"真心有型，大陸既應該咩都唔用 爛身爛世俾老豆老母推去乞食"},{"pid":"4d0ced054ca